‚ÄúI can only say thank you, and thank you, and thank you.‚Äù
In October 2017, football fan Steve Ware suffered a cardiac arrest whilst watching a Crystal Palace game at Selhurst Park. One minute he was fine, the next minute he had collapsed.
Stadium first aider Patricia Ashwood was the first to reach Steve. She acted quickly and calmly, immediately beginning CPR. Patricia saved Steve‚Äôs life.
Our volunteers make us who we are, and we're exceptionally proud of the difference they make out in their local communities.
